HEADWORD: Mi
<hw>Mi</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A syllable applied to the third tone of the scale
of C, <it>i. e.</it>, to E, in European solmization, but to the third
tone of any scale in the American system.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miamis</ent>⟦br⟧
